                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d482">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94119/709a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-04T21:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 4, 1940—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>519. For your confidential information the American Ambassador at Moscow reports
                    that his Japanese colleague has informed him that practically no progress has
                    been made in the efforts of the Japanese Government toward arranging directly
                    with General Chiang Kai-shek a peace between China and Japan.</p>
                <p>Sent to Tokyo via Shanghai. Repeated to Chungking, Peiping, Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
